snippet.title: USA: Residents react as San Francisco makes face masks mandatory
snippet.description:
Subscribe to our channel! rupt.ly/subscribe

San Francisco began enforcing its new mandatory policy on the use of masks while in public spaces on Wednesday, in a bid to halt the spread of the novel coronavirus.

Footage shows people walking around the city both with and without masks. 

San Francisco resident Travis said he wasn't against wearing a mask, but "there are not that many cases in San Francisco. If we were in New York City I would be wearing it for the last two weeks."

"I think the face mask makes sense, there's a lot of different opinions about it but it can't hurt," said resident Lee Cox after applauding San Francisco mayor London Breed for taking "early action to shut down and have us shelter in place."

"We have to do what we can to lower the curve. And if it takes a few more months of acting strangely, acting atypically, that's good, because these are atypical times," said San Francisco resident Allen.

Masks are now compulsory in six Bay Area counties including Alameda, Contra Costa, Marin, San Francisco, San Mateo, and Sonoma.

The extent of fines expected for those who defy the policy is as of yet unclear, with shops reportedly not allowing entrance to customers without a mask.

California has 33,261 confirmed cases of coronavirus and 1,268 related deaths as of Thursday morning, according to Johns Hopkins University.

snippet.title: Make Face Mask From a Bra | Easy DIY
snippet.description:
Who knew your bra could help prevent Coronavirus? Well, however surprising & absurd it may sound, but it‚Äôs true that you can use your bra to make a face mask. Here's how. 

Step 1: Take an old padded bra, preferably of cotton.
Step 2: You would need only one cup for the mask so cut the bra from the centre.
Step 3: Then you need to cut the sideband of the bra.
Step 4: Next we cut the strap and save it for the next step.
Step 5: Now we stitch the strap from one end of the cup to the other. You can also use a strong adhesive for this.
Voila, your DIY bra face mask is now ready to use!#bra #hacks #facemask

snippet.title: How to Make a DIY Simple Clay Face Mask!
snippet.description:
Your face is usually the first thing people see. No matter whether you struggle with a combination, dry, or oily skin type, this purifying mud clay mask can help you put your best face forward.
We‚Äôve created this Moroccan rhassoul clay facial mask and essential oil blend recipe to help draw out impurities, remove dead skin cells, and give you the glowing skin you‚Äôve been looking for without over-drying.
Like the popular bentonite clay or Dead Sea mud, Moroccan rhassoul clay is naturally derived from volcanic deposits and can assist in absorbing excess oil without having to turn to expensive spa treatments or chemically harsh skin care products.

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon Rhassoul Clay or Kaolin Clay
1 tablespoon aloe vera gel
1 tablespoon water
5 drops Geranium essential oil
3 drops Tea Tree essential oil
2 drops Lemon essential oil 

Instructions
Mix all the ingredients together to form a thick paste. Add more water and aloe vera 1 teaspoon at a time if you want the mixture to be thinner. The mask should be thick enough that you can spread it on easily.

To use
1. Apply the mask evenly to a clean, dry face with your fingers. 
2. Let the mask dry for 10-15 minutes; you don‚Äôt need to wait for it to dry fully. 
3. Rinse well, pat dry, and apply a light moisturizer. 
4. Use once a week.
5. Store paste in an airtight jar for up to a month. 

YL tip: Combination skin? Apply the mask only to your oily areas to avoid over-drying the dry parts of your skin.

Want to learn more? Check out our blog post here:

snippet.title: Why do Asians wear face masks? Do they wear masks just for Corona virus prevention?
snippet.description:
#how_to_make_FACE_MASK
Why do Asians wear face masks? Do they wear face masks just for Corona virus prevention?
Everywhere, you can see Asian people wearing face masks. 
In Japan, Korea, China, Vietnam, face masks have been being a part of daily life.
When there is a flu outbreak during cold season, adults and children will wear masks.
Another reason is air pollution.
Industrial cities and a great number of vehicles will pollute the air.
For sun protection
If you ride a motorcycle, you will need a mask.
It not only filters the air, but also prevents insects flying into your face at high speed.
Face mask is also effective against allergies when sensitive people breathe in pollen.
Asian countries with icy winters,a mask is also useful to protect the face.
Another use of mask for women is covering their bare face when they have no time to make up. Just brush some mascara and wear a mask, you also look great.
The mask also covers imperfections on the face.
They wear face masks to cover wounds, imperfections on the face. 
Another reason that makes a face mask popular in East Asian countries is helping people hide their emotions.
If you don't want to share your sadness or joy with others, a mask will help you.
Asian people wear face masks so often that for so long they have been a part of their wardrobe. There is even a fashion industry of face masks.
There are many models of face masks for people.
Sometimes face masks are beautifully decorated, elegant. Sometimes they are decorated in funny ways.
When Corona virus outbreak is found, it is recommended to wear a face mask properly and wash hands frequently according to WHO guidelines.
The face mask has no effective protection against Corona virus but it helps us limit the action of sneezing, coughing to the surrounding environment. Importantly, it helps people reduce the habit of touching their eyes, nose, and mouth. 
This will reduce the risk of getting infection for you, your family and the community.
